#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:1
msgid "Unsafety"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:3
msgid "Justify every use of `unsafe` (`justify-unsafe-use`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:5
msgid ""
"Every `unsafe` block must have a preceding `// SAFETY:` comment that "
"justifies why the operation is sound. For multi-condition invariants, use a "
"numbered list:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:11
msgid ""
"// SAFETY:\n"
"// 1. We have exclusive access to both the current context\n"
"//    and the next context (see above).\n"
"// 2. The next context is valid (because it is either\n"
"//    correctly initialized or written by a previous\n"
"//    `context_switch`).\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:22
msgid ""
"See also: PR [\\#2958](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/2958) and "
"[\\#836](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/pull/836)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:26
msgid "Document safety conditions (`document-safety-conds`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:28
msgid ""
"All `unsafe` functions and traits must include a `# Safety` section in their "
"doc comments describing the conditions, properties, or invariants that "
"callers must uphold. State exactly what the caller must guarantee — not "
"implementation details or side effects."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:35
msgid ""
"/// A marker trait for guard types that enforce the atomic mode.\n"
"///\n"
"/// # Safety\n"
"///\n"
"/// The implementer must ensure that the atomic mode is maintained while\n"
"/// the guard type is alive.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:44
msgid "Deny unsafe code in `kernel/` (`deny-unsafe-kernel`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:46
msgid "All crates under `kernel/` must deny unsafe:"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:52
msgid ""
"Only OSTD (`ostd/`) crates may contain `unsafe` code. If a kernel crate "
"requires an unsafe operation, the functionality should be provided as a safe "
"API in OSTD."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:56
msgid "Reason about safety at the module boundary (`module-boundary-safety`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:58
msgid ""
"The safety of an `unsafe` block depends on ALL code that can access the same "
"private state. Encapsulate unsafe abstractions in the smallest possible "
"module to minimize the \"audit surface.\" Any code in the same module that "
"can modify relied-upon fields is part of the safety argument."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:68
msgid "// Good — small, focused module limits the audit surface\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:70
msgid "/// Invariant: `next` is always a valid frame index.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:73
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/rust-guidelines/language-items/unsafety.md:78
msgid ""
"// SAFETY: `next` is always valid (see invariant above).\n"
"            // Only code in this module can modify `next`.\n"
msgstr ""
